# Tablet Photo Frame Constraints

## Environment & Deployment
- Package Manager: Yarn only (do not use npm).
- Local Media Source: /Users/robbintapper/Desktop/frame/
- Prod Server: root@192.168.68.50 (Key auth, directory: /opt/slideshow)
- Process Manager: PM2 (App name: slideshow)
- Deploy Command: git push && ssh root@192.168.68.50 'cd /opt/slideshow && git pull origin main && pm2 restart slideshow'
- Deploy Rule: Always run the Deploy Command automatically after committing any code change, without waiting to be asked.
- Git Rule: Prod branch has no upstream tracking. Always use explicit 'git pull origin main'.

## Gitignored Runtime Files (Exist on server only)
- config.json (slideshow settings)
- meta.json (media metadata mapping)
- server.config.json (ports and limits)
- ha_sync.json ({ "url": "http://192.168.68.140:8123", "token": "..." })

## Home Assistant Configuration Mappings
- interval -> input_number.slideshow_interval
- transition -> input_select.slideshow_transition
- kenBurns -> input_boolean.slideshow_ken_burns
- kenBurnsSpeed -> input_select.slideshow_ken_burns_speed
- order -> input_select.slideshow_order
- fit -> input_select.slideshow_fit

## Home Assistant Sync
- HA Host: root@192.168.68.140 (Key auth)
- HA Config: /homeassistant/configuration.yaml
- Sync Rule: Adding `/api/remote/*` to `server.js` requires appending a matching `rest_command` to HA Config.
- Reload Command:
  `ssh root@192.168.68.50 'TOKEN=$(python3 -c "import json; print(json.load(open(\"/opt/slideshow/ha_sync.json\"))[\"token\"])") && curl -s -X POST http://192.168.68.140:8123/api/services/homeassistant/reload_all -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" -H "Content-Type: application/json"'`

## Code Editing Rules
- When changing any files, push them and the prod server pulls to be up to date.
- Target Files: slideshow.html and manage.html are over 1,500 lines. The apply_diff tool will fail on massive rewrites.
- Strict Rule: Never request huge block rewrites. Search for specific local text strings first, then output edits in tiny, targeted diff blocks.
- Style: Keep code comments minimal and chat responses brief to minimize token costs.
- Output Constraint: Use extreme telegraphic/dense language for explanations. Omit polite filler, introductory text, and conversational summaries. Output raw code blocks immediately. Explanations must be blunt bullet points only. Never compress XML tool tags or programming syntax.
